3. auth module — TWO separate flows sharing one module:

   Customer flow (open self-registration):
   - GET /auth/google → redirect to Google OAuth consent
   - GET /auth/google/callback → find or create user by Google email,
     issue access token + refresh token (httpOnly cookie)
   - POST /auth/refresh → validate refresh token, rotate it, detect reuse
     (if a token is used twice, revoke the whole token family, force re-login)
   - POST /auth/logout → revoke refresh token

   Staff flow (allowlist-gated):
   - GET /auth/staff/google, GET /auth/staff/google/callback
   - On callback: check the Google email against staff_allowlist table
     BEFORE creating any account or session. If not present, return 403
     with a generic message — do not reveal whether the email exists elsewhere
     in the system. If present, create/update the staff record and issue
     tokens carrying a role claim.

   Store only a SHA-256 hash of refresh tokens in the DB, never the raw token.

